						               													<description>This game is very close to a movie franchise (1984 till 2009), and a tv series (2007 till 2009) - in which machines try to kill a future leader by sending back in time certain characters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game pits players against each other in two teams: The Mechanical Assassins and the Resistance Fighters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Depending on your allegiance your personal goals are set. Reach them, and support your team mates and you will win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All players travel as a group to different locations in time.&amp;#10;The current (active) player asks the group to perform a certain action, which is then voted upon. Success: and s/he may either hack, attack, or (possibly) kill someone, or succeed at this time's mission to gain an artifact/item. Fail: and it is the next players turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Items grant special abilites (skip certain votes), but may have a limited usage. They also may change the might of a character in the vote.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends, when John C. (son of Sarah C.) dies, or all possible time locations having been explored.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Depending on the individual goals, a total is made for both teams, who ever has the higher wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game was created for the http://www.boardgamegeek.com/thread/974256/pnp-hidden-role-bluffing-card-game-design-contest in 2013&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
